.TH DAPS 1 "2026-07-03" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Document Processing Tools"
.SH NAME
daps \- Autologic APS-5 phototypesetter troff back-end
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B daps
.RI "[\-t] [\-D" dir "] [" file " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B daps
is the troff back-end for the historical Autologic APS-5
phototypesetter. It reads device-independent
.BR troff (1)
output (the ditroff intermediate representation) and produces
APS-5 job code.
.PP
The port ships
.B daps
for completeness but few users will exercise it; it is retained
because Ritter's original toolset drives real APS-5 hardware
in some museums and archives.
.SH HEIRLOOM DARWIN PORT
Supports the shared modality flags. See
.BR heirloom-modality (7).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR troff (1),
.BR dpost (1).
